<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>

<div>
<h2>Serious Fire</h2>

<p>On Sunday 30th October a major fire at the University’s Highfield Campus has partially destroyed the Mountbatten Building, in particular the area containing the Silicon Fabrication Facility. Fortunately, no-one was injured or is missing as a result of the fire.</p>
<p>Information and guidance is available from the <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://totl.net/ECS/wiki.pl">temporary ECS wiki</a> and what was the <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/fire2005/">temporary ECS website</a>.</p>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/808"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_808_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=fe0d871248bdc4d98017f7bf40f3d26a&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="" title="" border="0" width="104" height="150" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2 class="hide">Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/808">Gathering of world’s experts in pattern analysis</a></h3><p>A workshop which will bring together the world’s top researchers in pattern analysis will take place this week. The Analysis of Patterns workshop, co-organized by Professor John Shawe-Taylor, Head of the ECS Information: Signals, Images and Systems group, will take place at the Centre Ettore Majorana for Scientific Culture in Erice, Italy from 28 October to 6 November 2005, and enable the world’s scientific communities committed to developing common principles of modern pattern analysis to come together and share their experiences.</p><p></p></div></div><div class='rightside'>
<div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359/http://www2006.org"><img style="border: 0" src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051107091359im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/www2006logo.small.png" /></a></div>
</div>
